OL,6,FMr Mainstone went onto say that
OL,7,FPennington later refused to take his
OL,8,Fwife to a hair appointment, so she had
OL,9,Fto go by taxi.
OL,11,FThe court heard how he was also said
OL,12,Fto become abusive after drinking and
OL,13,Fdid so on the evening of 16 August.
OL,14,FFearing something would happen Ms
OL,15,FLloyd began recording their
OL,16,Fconversation on her mobile phone.
OL,18,FMr Mainstone said Pennington grabbed
OL,19,Fher hair and dragged her from room to
OL,20,Froom then slapped her and head-butted
OL,21,Fher above her left eye.
