OL,6,FMr Mainstone said there was
OL,7,Fhumiliation, degradation and a fear of
OL,8,Fviolence. He concluded it was a
OL,9,F"disability hate crime" over not just
OL,10,Fthe day in question but over three
OL,11,Fyears.
OL,13,FRecordings of the abusive behaviour
OL,14,Fwere played in court and Gareth
OL,15,FBellis, defending, accepted they were
OL,16,Fa "harrowing listen." He was clearly
OL,17,Facting completely and utterly out of
OL,18,Fcontrol in drink," said the barrister.
